{"sequence":39,"timestamp":"2026-04-07T06:47:24.051215892Z","event_type":"amendment_queued","details":{"amendment_id":"fr-2-c0e029c2","body":"In resolve_final_review_panel_for_preflight (engine.rs:367-397), the planner and arbiter are resolved twice: once explicitly with preflight error wrapping, then again inside resolve_final_review_panel (which internally calls resolve_final_review_planner_target and resolves the arbiter via final_review_policy().arbiter_backend). The explicit results are then overwritten onto the panel. Since resolve_final_review_panel already uses the correct dedicated resolution paths, the separate explicit resolution + overwrite is redundant. Simplify to either: (a) delegate entirely to resolve_final_review_panel like the prompt_review case was simplified, or (b) stop calling resolve_final_review_panel and resolve reviewers directly to assemble the panel manually. The current double-resolution pattern is fragile — if someone later changes arbiter resolution logic inside resolve_final_review_panel without updating the preflight wrapper (or vice versa), the overwritten values would silently mask the divergence.","dedup_key":"1ef8e3914bd2a7bc58274041089c07d5fe484fe6ed8feeb4a5e724c8d30affa9","reviewer_sources":[{"backend_family":"claude","model_id":"claude-opus-4-6","reviewer_id":"reviewer-1"}],"run_id":"run-20260407053506","source":"workflow_stage","source_stage":"final_review"}}
{"sequence":40,"timestamp":"2026-04-07T06:47:24.061332229Z","event_type":"amendment_queued","details":{"amendment_id":"fr-2-cff2c8b7","body":"Restore member-specific prompt-review preflight errors in `src/contexts/workflow_composition/engine.rs:352-364`. The new `resolve_prompt_review_panel_for_preflight` wrapper now rewrites every resolution failure to `prompt-review panel resolution failed`, so a broken `prompt_review.refiner_backend` is no longer distinguishable from validator-panel failures. Keep the dedicated-override behavior, but preserve refiner-specific failure attribution the way the final-review helper now does for planner/arbiter.","dedup_key":"f9d34b563391dc1f52357c921ddc747a7258decddcae0fbf1a188b63b42a8767","reviewer_sources":[{"backend_family":"codex","model_id":"gpt-5.4","reviewer_id":"reviewer-2"}],"run_id":"run-20260407053506","source":"workflow_stage","source_stage":"final_review"}}
{"sequence":41,"timestamp":"2026-04-07T06:47:24.071279378Z","event_type":"amendment_queued","details":{"amendment_id":"fr-2-8f5d9eba","body":"Add an engine-level regression test for the actual final-review fix path. The runtime change is in `src/contexts/workflow_composition/engine.rs:367-395`, but the new coverage in `tests/unit/backend_policy_test.rs:369-390` only exercises `BackendPolicyService::resolve_final_review_panel`, which already resolved the dedicated planner correctly before this patch. Extend `tests/unit/workflow_engine_test.rs` near `2040-2068` with a case where `workflow.planner_backend` is invalid/unavailable and `final_review.planner_backend` is valid, then assert `preflight_check` honors the dedicated final-review planner target.","dedup_key":"fd3f426b235c3e0394b2b0a6fa1e585b61108342b22a54fe7dc32364b528e966","reviewer_sources":[{"backend_family":"codex","model_id":"gpt-5.4","reviewer_id":"reviewer-2"}],"run_id":"run-20260407053506","source":"workflow_stage","source_stage":"final_review"}}
